p: Overall, RWHAP providers located in rural areas were funded to deliver a greater number of service categories per site than non-rural providers (44.7% funded for ≥5 services vs. 34.1% funded for ≥5 services, respectively; Table 3). Whereas 11.0% of non-rural providers were funded only for support services, 2.3% of rural providers were funded for support services only. Compared to non-rural providers, a greater proportion of rural providers were funded for oral health care (44.7% vs. 27.8%); medical case management (57.6% vs. 47.3%); outpatient ambulatory health services (53.0% vs. 43.0%); early intervention services (24.2% vs. 16.3%); non-medical case management (38.6% vs. 30.7%); emergency financial assistance (25.8% vs. 18.4%); and food bank /home delivered meals (23.5% vs. 15.1%).
